function onTick() clock = input.getNumber(1) cStart = input.getNumber(2) cStop = input.getNumber(3) if cStart == cStop then output.setBool(1,true) elseif cStart > cStop and (clock >= cStart or clock <= cStop) then output.setBool(1,true) elseif cStart < cStop and (clock >= cStart and clock <= cStop) then output.setBool(1,true) else output.setBool(1,false) end end

object.script:
mapZ = 0.7 locked = true pSize = 4
function onTick() w = input.getNumber(1) h = input.getNumber(2) if h<96 then pSize=2 else pSize=4 end tx = input.getNumber(3) ty = input.getNumber(4) fk = input.getBool(1) moveable = property.getBool("Map Moveable") bPos = property.getNumber("Buttons Position") gpsX = input.getNumber(11) gpsY = input.getNumber(12) if mapX == nil and gpsX ~= 0 then mapX = gpsX mapY = gpsY end end
function onDraw() local mvSpdX=0.7 local mvSpdY=0.5 local scale local nb = 3 if not moveable then nb = 2 end local bW = w/nb local barHeight = math.floor(h / 10) if barHeight < 6 then barHeight = 6 end local barTop = h-barHeight local barBot = h local mapTop = 0 local mapBot = h-barHeight-1
if bPos == 2 then barTop = 0 barBot = barHeight mapTop = barHeight + 1 mapBot = h end if move then if locked then newX = gpsX newY = gpsY end mapX = math.floor(mapX*100)/100 mapY = math.floor(mapY*100)/100 lX = math.sqrt((newX-mapX)^2) lY = math.sqrt((newY-mapY)^2) mvSpdX = mvSpdX * (lX / 10) mvSpdY = mvSpdY * (lY / 10) if newX > mapX then mapX = mapX+mvSpdX end if newX < mapX then mapX = mapX-mvSpdX end if newY > mapY then mapY = mapY+mvSpdY end if newY < mapY then mapY = mapY-mvSpdY end if lX < 0.15 and lY < 0.25 then move = false end end if (locked and not move) or not moveable then mapX = gpsX mapY = gpsY end screen.drawMap(mapX, mapY, mapZ) local sX, sY = map.mapToScreen(mapX, mapY, mapZ, w, h, gpsX, gpsY) screen.setColor(90, 0, 0) screen.drawCircle(sX, sY, pSize) if moveable then if scrP(fk,1,bW-1,barTop,barBot) then locked = true move = true screen.setColor(0, 27, 41) else screen.setColor(0, 94, 142) end screen.drawRectF(0, barTop, bW, barHeight) end scale = 0.05 * (mapZ/2)
if not minD and scrP(fk,bW*(nb-2)+1,bW*(nb-1)-1,barTop,barBot) then screen.setColor(0, 27, 41) mapZ = mapZ + scale plusD = false if mapZ >= 15 then mapZ = 15 minD = true end elseif minD then screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) else screen.setColor(0, 94, 142) end screen.drawRectF(bW*(nb-2), barTop, bW, barHeight)
if not plusD and scrP(fk,bW*(nb-1)+1,w,barTop,barBot) then screen.setColor(0, 27, 41) mapZ = mapZ - scale minD = false if mapZ <= 0.1 then mapZ = 0.1 plusD = true end elseif plusD then screen.setColor(20, 20, 20) else screen.setColor(0, 94, 142) end screen.drawRectF(bW*(nb-1), barTop, bW, barHeight) if scrP(fk,0,w,mapTop,mapBot) and moveable then newX, newY = map.screenToMap(mapX, mapY, mapZ, w, h, tx, ty) newX = math.floor(newX*100)/100 newY = math.floor(newY*100)/100 locked = false move = true end screen.setColor(15, 15, 15) screen.drawLine(bW ,barTop, bW, barBot) if moveable then screen.drawLine(bW*2 ,barTop, bW*2, barBot) end screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) if moveable then screen.drawText(bW/2-2, barBot-(barHeight/2)-2, "R") end screen.drawText((bW*(nb-2))+bW/2-2, barBot-(barHeight/2)-2, "-") screen.drawText((bW*(nb-1))+bW/2-2, barBot-(barHeight/2)-2, "+") end
function scrP(k, x, x2, y, y2) return tx >= x and tx <= x2 and ty >= y and ty <= y2 and k end

node.label: Compass Direction
node.description: From compass sensor. For calibrating wind direction. Make sure compass is pointing in the same direction as wind sensor.

object.script:
-- ORIGINAL WEATHER SCRIPT BY DTplayers (edited for this mission)
windSpd = 0 windDir = 0 rain = 0 humid = 0 time = 0
formattedTime = "" weather = "" visibility = ""
function onTick() time = input.getNumber(1) compassDir = input.getNumber(2) * -1 windSpd = input.getNumber(3) windDir = input.getNumber(4) rain = input.getNumber(5) humid = input.getNumber(6) end
function onDraw() --wind direction local newWindDir = windDir + compassDir + 0.5 newWindDir = newWindDir - math.floor(newWindDir)
--time local minutes = math.floor((1440 * time) % 60) local hours = math.floor(24 * time)
if minutes < 10 then minutes = '0' .. minutes end if hours < 10 then hours = '0' .. hours end
formattedTime = hours .. ':' .. minutes
--weather --screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) if rain < 0.01 then weather = 'No Rain' elseif rain < 0.50 then weather = 'Light Rain' --screen.setColor(252, 233, 3) elseif rain < 0.70 then weather = 'Rainy' --screen.setColor(255, 140, 0) elseif rain < 0.90 then weather = 'Heavy Rain' --screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) else weather = 'Stormy' end
--visibility if humid < 0.10 then visibility = 'Good' elseif humid < 0.40 then visibility = 'Moderate' else visibility = 'Poor' end
--wind alert if windSpd<5 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawText(57, 27, 'WIND SPD : OK') elseif windSpd<=12 then screen.setColor(255, 30, 0) screen.drawText(57, 27, 'WIND SPD : WARNING') else screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawText(57, 27, 'WIND SPD : CRITICAL') end
--rain alert if rain<=0.30 then screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawText(57, 35, 'FORECAST : OK') elseif rain<0.50 then screen.setColor(255, 30, 0) screen.drawText(57, 35, 'FORECAST : WARNING') else screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawText(57, 35, 'FORECAST : CRITICAL') end
--fake alert screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawText(57, 51, 'GLOBAL #1 : OK') screen.drawText(57, 59, 'GLOBAL #2 : OK') screen.drawText(57, 67, 'GLOBAL #3 : OFFLINE') screen.drawText(57, 75, 'GLOBAL #4 : OK')
--screen w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
screen.setColor(10, 10, 11) screen.drawRectF(0, 0, 52, h) screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawLine(52, 0, 52, h) screen.drawLine(0, 16, 52, 16) screen.drawLine(0, 75, 52, 75)
screen.drawText(70, 5, 'WEATHER STATUS') screen.drawText(77, 12, 'FOR LANDING')
screen.drawText(1, 2, formattedTime)
-- test colored weather --if rain < 0.01 then weather = screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) --elseif rain < 0.50 then weather = screen.setColor(252, 233, 3) --elseif rain < 0.70 then weather = screen.setColor(255, 140, 0) --elseif rain < 0.90 then weather = screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) --else weather = screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) --end
screen.drawText(1, 9, weather) screen.drawText(1, 19, 'Wind') screen.drawText(1, 26, math.floor((windSpd * 1.943844) + 0.5) .. ' kias') screen.drawText(1, 33, math.floor((newWindDir * 360) + 0.5) .. ' deg') screen.drawText(1, 80, 'Visibility') screen.drawText(1, 87, visibility)
screen.drawRectF(25, 53, 3, 3) screen.setColor(0, 200, 0)
newWindDir = newWindDir * 6.283185 screen.drawLine(26, 54, 26 + (math.sin(newWindDir) * math.min(windSpd, 15)), 54 + (math.cos(newWindDir) * math.min(windSpd, 15) * -1))
end

function onTick() elec = input.getNumber(1) fuel = input.getNumber(2) temp = input.getNumber(3) rps = input.getNumber(4) alti = input.getNumber(5) tfuel = input.getNumber(6) radio = input.getNumber(9) alarm = input.getBool(1) legs = input.getBool(2) telec = 10
if tfuel and tfuel>0 then pfuel = fuel/tfuel*100 pelec = elec/telec*100 else pfuel = nil telec = nil end end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawTextBox(0, 5, w, h, "FACLON HEAVY - REALTIME DATA", 0, -1) screen.drawRect(0, 15, 160, 0)
if pfuel then screen.drawText(5, 20, "Main Electric "..round(pelec).."%") screen.drawText(5, 30, "Engine Temp ".."-NO DATA-") screen.drawText(5, 40, "Engine RPS "..round(rps)) screen.drawText(5, 50, "Altitude "..round(alti)) screen.drawText(5, 60, "Radio Signal "..roundbis(radio).."%") else screen.drawText(5, 20, "Main Electric ".."-NO DATA-") screen.drawText(5, 30, "Engine Temp ".."-NO DATA-") screen.drawText(5, 40, "Engine RPS ".."-NO DATA-") screen.drawText(5, 50, "Altimeter ".."-NO DATA-") screen.drawText(5, 60, "Radio Signal ".."-NO DATA-") end screen.drawRect(0, 20, 0, 5) screen.drawRect(0, 30, 0, 5) screen.drawRect(0, 40, 0, 5) screen.drawRect(0, 50, 0, 5) screen.drawRect(0, 60, 0, 5)
screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawRectF(0, 73, 160, 19) screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawText(5, 75, "Booster Legs ")
if legs then screen.setColor(218, 104, 15) screen.drawText(90, 75, "RETRACTED") else screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawText(90, 75, "FAILURE") end
if not pfuel then screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawText(5, 85, "Fuel Level ".."-NO DATA-") elseif alarm then screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawText(5, 85, "LOW FUEL "..round(pfuel).."%") else screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawText(5, 85, "Fuel Level "..round(pfuel).."%") end end
function round(n) return math.floor(n*100+0.5)/100 end
function roundbis(n) return math.floor(n*100+0.5) end
